column5: Hanging out a Jiggy for a few days, heres some pics...  Followed this guy up.. hopefully its the only time I see the facilities from that angle.    Had a thunderstorm blow through and provide us with a great rainbow!!      Had oysters for the first time up here, they are keeping very welll    And heres some fish.. ya ya I know Im not in any of the pictures, someone has to guide her!!!!
Nice pics TJ. Good to see at least Monique is catching the fish up there...Oh and love the pic of buddy towing the pooper,priceless !!
Nice Pics TJ. I know as we get older, we gotta GO more often, but taking your own crapper on the road with you is a bit of overkill, don't ya think?
Great pics TJ.  After your first post about that Salton icemaker, I went and bought one and love it.  Gonna take it camping for sure
TJ.. when you heading for town for beer ??
Thanks guys.. lol.. umm not heading to town until Tuesday!!
Tuesday eh... I'd better get out in the hangar and get that last wiring finished up!
That place looks pretty peaceful..and looks to have some great fish.
now i know who puts the fish on the table congrats to the both of you
Love that last pic of the 15hp Johnson.....sunset isn't bad either
Yep, life is good when you do it right.
nice pics boss !!! by the way i dont think we have seen you in a pic holding a fish you have caught in a long,long time !!!...whats up with that ???? lol..lol place looks awesome...
